    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Sheet music that has been bound. The sheets may have been assembled and bound for a variety of reasons, including professional musicians’ volumes, music bound for publishers, music stores, or door to door sales, or as keepsakes, assembled primarily by women of the middle- and upper-classes during their formative years of musical training. For volumes of music that were created as bound volumes, use "music books."</Note_Text>
